1
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,280
What a fine poem!

2
00:01:26,719 --> 00:01:27,359
Wonderful!

3
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:31,159
"Farewell, my lord; Loulan was won in a night."

4
00:01:31,319 --> 00:01:32,920
I never imagined one so young

5
00:01:33,079 --> 00:01:34,560
could possess such literary depth.

6
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:35,480
Once this poem spreads,

7
00:01:35,599 --> 00:01:37,519
your name will surely shake the capital.

8
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,719
I have no desire to shake the capital.

9
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:44,400
All I want is a full belly.

10
00:01:45,079 --> 00:01:45,920
But why?

11
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,719
Fame brings trouble, like fat to a pig.

12
00:01:49,159 --> 00:01:50,239
If my name became renowned,

13
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,599
the Ning household would never tolerate me.

14
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:58,319
A mouthful of absurd words,

15
00:01:58,920 --> 00:01:59,640
a handful

16
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:02,400
of bitter tears.

17
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:04,799
All in the world bear hardships,

18
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:06,560
but who can grasp

19
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:10,400
the taste within?

20
00:02:13,479 --> 00:02:13,879
You...

21
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,719
Speak plainly!

22
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,159
Plain words, please.

23
00:02:18,479 --> 00:02:19,759
Can you even understand?

24
00:02:20,319 --> 00:02:22,000
It means I'm having a hard time.

25
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:24,759
The great recluse hides in the city,

26
00:02:24,879 --> 00:02:26,120
the lesser recluse hides in the wilds.

27
00:02:26,319 --> 00:02:28,000
Heaven and earth, vast and primordial,

28
00:02:28,159 --> 00:02:29,120
each follows its own path.

29
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:32,199
Why trouble oneself needlessly?

30
00:02:32,879 --> 00:02:33,319
Enough of that.

31
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,159
My young friend,

32
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,120
this poem of yours,

33
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:37,360
how much silver will you sell it for?

34
00:02:39,599 --> 00:02:40,719
Since Uncle has treated me to a meal,

35
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,039
I'll be straightforward.

36
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,960
One hundred taels, as before.

37
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:44,719
Done.

38
00:02:50,159 --> 00:02:52,159
Many thanks, Uncle Tianxuan.

39
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,039
This is exactly what I like about you.

40
00:02:55,199 --> 00:02:55,800
Forthright.

41
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,080
The hour grows late today,

42
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,439
so I won't keep you any longer.

43
00:02:59,719 --> 00:03:01,879
If you compose new verses in the future,

44
00:03:02,039 --> 00:03:04,199
Find me at Top Scholar Pavilion anytime.

45
00:03:06,199 --> 00:03:07,800
Rest assured, Uncle Tianxuan.

46
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:10,080
Until we meet again.

47
00:03:12,319 --> 00:03:13,000
Farewell.

48
00:03:13,639 --> 00:03:14,120
After you.

49
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,039
And you,

50
00:03:18,479 --> 00:03:19,199
farewell.

51
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,080
Your Majes— Master.

52
00:03:26,439 --> 00:03:28,319
If this poem is released,

53
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,439
your reputation

54
00:03:29,599 --> 00:03:32,159
will surely rise to new heights.

55
00:03:35,639 --> 00:03:37,159
You want me to pass it off as my own?

56
00:03:38,199 --> 00:03:39,400
Though I'm fond of poetry,

57
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:42,159
I wouldn't stoop to claiming false fame.

58
00:03:42,759 --> 00:03:44,680
This servant thought since we paid for it,

59
00:03:44,879 --> 00:03:46,840
the poem's already ours, isn't it?

60
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:49,560
You really think they're worth 250 taels?

61
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:53,080
These poems are priceless.

62
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:54,319
The reason I gave him 250 taels

63
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:55,879
is because he's young and frail.

64
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,479
I feared carrying too much wealth

65
00:03:57,639 --> 00:03:58,879
might bring disaster upon him.

66
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:02,800
You truly think of everything, Master.

67
00:04:03,479 --> 00:04:05,199
Copy these poems out

68
00:04:05,439 --> 00:04:07,919
and send them to officials in the capital.

69
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:10,439
Let them study and admire them properly.

70
00:04:11,879 --> 00:04:13,719
This lad has such talent,

71
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:16,720
he can't be from an ordinary family.

72
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:19,199
Though his clothes are plain,

73
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,240
there must be more to him.

74
00:04:22,439 --> 00:04:25,000
Shall this servant go investigate?

75
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:26,839
Yes, look into it.

76
00:04:27,759 --> 00:04:30,279
This lad is a promising one.

77
00:04:31,839 --> 00:04:32,560
Yes, sir.

78
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,040
Xiao Mei.

79
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,680
Chicken for dinner tonight!

80
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:42,560
Where is everyone?

81
00:04:42,639 --> 00:04:43,399
You stop right there!

82
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:44,120
Hold on,

83
00:04:44,519 --> 00:04:46,920
I only had one cup of your wine.

84
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,639
Come on, is it really that serious?

85
00:04:48,759 --> 00:04:49,120
Stop!

86
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,079
You shrew!

87
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:52,079
I just took your money— I'll kill you!

88
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,720
—for wine! You old cripple!

89
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,560
Still running?

90
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,560
What's going on?

91
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:55,800
I...

92
00:04:55,839 --> 00:04:57,279
Help! I'll beat you to death!

93
00:04:57,759 --> 00:04:58,759
Help!

94
00:04:58,839 --> 00:04:59,439
Don't run!

95
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:02,920
You stand right here!

96
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:04,519
See if I don't beat you to death!

97
00:05:04,519 --> 00:05:05,560
If I don't run, you'd kill me!

98
00:05:05,759 --> 00:05:06,879
I'm not stupid!

99
00:05:07,079 --> 00:05:07,279
You!

100
00:05:07,279 --> 00:05:07,920
Sister-in-law, sister-in-law!

101
00:05:08,079 --> 00:05:08,720
What happened?

102
00:05:09,279 --> 00:05:10,120
You've got the nerve to ask?

103
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:11,519
My dear sister kindly

104
00:05:11,639 --> 00:05:12,720
took you two in,

105
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,120
but this old wretch

106
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:16,160
actually stole our money to buy wine!

107
00:05:16,519 --> 00:05:17,240
Do you have any idea?

108
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,240
That money

109
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,519
was saved by our family scrimping on

110
00:05:20,879 --> 00:05:22,680
food and clothes for Mei Shi's schooling!

111
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:24,560
You!

112
00:05:27,399 --> 00:05:28,600
You damned old cripple!

113
00:05:28,759 --> 00:05:29,600
Give me back my silver!

114
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,680
I want to go to school!

115
00:05:30,879 --> 00:05:31,720
Give back my silver!

116
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:32,839
Give me back my silver!

117
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:33,319
What's going on?

118
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,120
Give back my money!

119
00:05:34,319 --> 00:05:35,319
I want to go to school! Stop shouting!

120
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,720
What have I always taught you?

121
00:05:36,879 --> 00:05:37,399
Where are your manners?

122
00:05:38,519 --> 00:05:39,360
The money's been stolen!

123
00:05:39,519 --> 00:05:40,279
Why bother with manners?

124
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:40,959
Money!

125
00:05:40,959 --> 00:05:41,399
Sister.

126
00:05:41,639 --> 00:05:43,040
Don't blame me for being harsh today.

127
00:05:43,319 --> 00:05:44,399
Either they pay back the money today,

128
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,279
or we go to the authorities.

129
00:05:45,639 --> 00:05:46,360
Sister-in-law, sister-in-law!

130
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:47,240
Don't get violent yet.

131
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:48,160
You see,

132
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,079
I happened to earn some money today.

133
00:05:52,399 --> 00:05:52,800
Here.

134
00:05:58,279 --> 00:05:59,279
One hundred taels.

135
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,040
Two hundred taels.

136
00:06:05,639 --> 00:06:07,040
Y-You... where did you get so much money?

137
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,399
Don't ask about that, sister-in-law.

138
00:06:09,079 --> 00:06:09,680
I don't even know yet

139
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,199
how many days I'll be imposing here.

140
00:06:11,399 --> 00:06:12,360
Take this money for now.

141
00:06:12,639 --> 00:06:13,560
Send the child to school first.

142
00:06:15,319 --> 00:06:16,160
I knew it.

143
00:06:16,279 --> 00:06:17,519
A young master from a noble family

144
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:19,120
couldn't possibly be short on silver.

145
00:06:19,439 --> 00:06:20,160
Wonderful!

146
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,959
With silver, I can go to school!

147
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:22,879
Yes.

148
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:24,399
My dear.

149
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:25,800
It's getting late.

150
00:06:26,319 --> 00:06:27,240
Go kill the chicken first.

151
00:06:27,639 --> 00:06:28,120
Right.

152
00:06:28,319 --> 00:06:29,240
A live chicken, nice and fresh.

153
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,360
We'll all eat together tonight.

154
00:06:30,519 --> 00:06:31,399
Just one chicken,

155
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,319
how can it feed all of us?

156
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:33,800
Tell you what,

157
00:06:34,079 --> 00:06:34,920
I'll prepare a few more dishes.

158
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:39,879
What are you two standing there for?

159
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,720
We're out of rice.

160
00:06:40,839 --> 00:06:42,360
Hurry, take the child and buy some.

161
00:06:43,199 --> 00:06:43,959
All right, all right.

162
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:48,639
You old swindler!

163
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,120
You started drinking first?

164
00:06:50,639 --> 00:06:52,240
Top Scholar Pavilion's Top Scholar's Brew.

165
00:06:52,399 --> 00:06:53,439
Fine wine!

166
00:06:55,959 --> 00:06:57,079
Quite the discerning palate.

167
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:58,160
So you know it's good, young master.

168
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,680
Your silver notes,

169
00:06:59,879 --> 00:07:01,680
they surely didn't come honestly.

170
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,560
I haven't settled the swindling with you,

171
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,160
and now you're turning on me?

172
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:07,399
Let me tell you,

173
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:08,439
this money

174
00:07:08,759 --> 00:07:10,319
was earned by yours truly.

175
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:11,279
Pfft!

176
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:12,680
Quit boasting.

177
00:07:12,839 --> 00:07:13,680
Do you even know

178
00:07:13,839 --> 00:07:15,639
what two hundred taels of silver means?

179
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:17,279
Your father, Ning Ziming,

180
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:19,199
as Minister of Rites,

181
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,240
earns only 150 taels a year.

182
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:23,959
A modest two-courtyard home in the capital

183
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,160
costs about that much.

184
00:07:25,399 --> 00:07:27,439
You're young and have no real skills,

185
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,319
can't shoulder a load or carry a thing.

186
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,120
And you... you...

187
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,480
I earned this myself!

188
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,959
Just confess honestly,

189
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,240
where did you steal it from?

190
00:07:34,439 --> 00:07:35,360
Exactly, young master.

191
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,959
Y-You're from a distinguished family.

192
00:07:37,319 --> 00:07:38,759
Though you're facing some hardships now,

193
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:39,399
still,

194
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:41,240
you mustn't resort to thievery!

195
00:07:42,399 --> 00:07:43,839
Young master, you're still young.

196
00:07:43,959 --> 00:07:45,000
If you go down the wrong path

197
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:46,600
and ruin your life, what then?

198
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,480
Fine, fine, fine.

199
00:07:52,319 --> 00:07:53,600
You all look down on me, do you?

200
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,040
Then today I'll tell you

201
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,480
exactly how I

202
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:02,519
stole this money.

203
00:08:03,319 --> 00:08:04,399
Shut up!

204
00:08:07,199 --> 00:08:08,680
Earned it!

205
00:08:17,879 --> 00:08:19,879
Reporting to Your Majesty.

206
00:08:24,199 --> 00:08:26,120
Was the poem bought today transcribed?

207
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,639
This servant has already sent men

208
00:08:28,839 --> 00:08:30,800
to deliver it to each official's home.

209
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:34,799
By the way,

210
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:38,240
the identity of the man who sold the poem

211
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,559
has been confirmed.

212
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:43,159
Minister of Rites Ning Ziming's bastard.

213
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,159
Ning Chen.

214
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,120
Ning Chen.

215
00:08:46,639 --> 00:08:48,559
Your Majesty, shall we have him arrested?

216
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,720
This is deceiving the Emperor!

217
00:08:52,559 --> 00:08:54,279
But he didn't know my identity.

218
00:08:54,559 --> 00:08:55,320
What crime has he committed?

219
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:59,080
However, since he is Ning Ziming's son,

220
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,919
why does he dress so shabbily?

221
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:01,960
And he even claimed

222
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,720
that all his family members were dead.

223
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:06,720
Ning Chen was exiled since childhood.

224
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:07,879
Eight years ago,

225
00:09:08,039 --> 00:09:08,879
Ning Ziming

226
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,440
brought him back home.

227
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,840
This fellow

228
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,679
isn't favored at home.

229
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,039
And Ning Ziming

230
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:17,960
rarely mentions this son in public.

231
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:22,000
I remember now.

232
00:09:22,519 --> 00:09:23,159
A few years ago,

233
00:09:23,279 --> 00:09:25,600
someone cited Minister Ning's abandonment

234
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:28,519
to impeach the Left Chancellor for laxity.

235
00:09:28,879 --> 00:09:31,360
At that time, I was at war with Tuoluo,

236
00:09:31,759 --> 00:09:32,840
overwhelmed with troubles,

237
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,480
and I forgot about this matter.

238
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:36,960
Well, well.

239
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,440
A dignified Minister of Rites,

240
00:09:38,559 --> 00:09:40,720
yet behaving like this behind the scenes.

241
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,360
It's time to give him a warning.

242
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:44,559
This is also a good chance

243
00:09:45,159 --> 00:09:46,960
for the other officials at court

244
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:48,840
to take heed of the lesson.

245
00:09:49,639 --> 00:09:50,440
Convey my decree.

246
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,759
Summon Ning Ziming to the palace.

247
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:52,879
Yes, Your Majesty.

248
00:09:58,039 --> 00:10:00,759
This is the poem His Majesty sent today

249
00:10:00,919 --> 00:10:02,600
to be circulated among the officials.

250
00:10:02,799 --> 00:10:03,480
Take a look.

251
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:08,960
What do you think?

252
00:10:11,039 --> 00:10:12,200
A profound and lofty meaning,

253
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,759
every word a gem.

254
00:10:14,799 --> 00:10:15,960
I feel ashamed by comparison.

255
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,039
If this man takes the imperial exam,

256
00:10:20,399 --> 00:10:22,080
I'd have no chance at being top scholar.

257
00:10:24,039 --> 00:10:24,879
No need to worry.

258
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,360
I've already had it investigated.

259
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:29,720
He hasn't entered the exam this year.

260
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:33,919
I never imagined our capital

261
00:10:34,879 --> 00:10:37,519
would have such a brilliantly talented man

262
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:39,360
who cares nothing for empty fame.

263
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:42,320
You three should follow his example.

264
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,240
Study diligently.

265
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,360
We shall remember, Father.

266
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,679
My lord, you are the Minister of Rites,

267
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,279
and their grandfather is Left Chancellor.

268
00:10:51,559 --> 00:10:52,840
Even if they aren't his equal,

269
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,360
with you paving the way for them,

270
00:10:54,759 --> 00:10:57,000
they'll rise swiftly through the ranks.

271
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:59,159
Why bother taking him seriously?

272
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:00,840
Mother is right.

273
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,440
Envoy Quan has arrived!

274
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,159
Envoy Quan!

275
00:11:08,279 --> 00:11:08,840
What a rare guest, rare indeed.

276
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,399
By His Majesty's decree,

277
00:11:12,679 --> 00:11:15,480
Ning Ziming is to enter the palace now.

278
00:11:16,279 --> 00:11:18,039
This subject obeys.

279
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:23,080
May I ask, Envoy,

280
00:11:23,559 --> 00:11:25,200
why His Majesty has summoned me

281
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,200
today?

282
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,480
You'll find out when you arrive.

283
00:11:30,399 --> 00:11:33,120
And is His Majesty pleased or displeased?

284
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,360
The Emperor's mind is like a deep abyss,

285
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:37,039
neither pleased nor angered.

286
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,799
My lord, you should set off quickly.

287
00:11:39,039 --> 00:11:41,080
Don't keep His Majesty waiting.

288
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,399
That old fox.

289
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,279
Unbelievable.

290
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:51,679
My lord.

291
00:11:52,559 --> 00:11:53,320
Could it be...

292
00:11:53,919 --> 00:11:56,120
that you and Father bribed for Gan'er,

293
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:57,639
and His Majesty found out?

294
00:11:57,840 --> 00:12:00,799
He's not the only official's son testing.

295
00:12:01,279 --> 00:12:02,519
Plenty of others bribe officials too.

296
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,399
You all wait here at home.

297
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:06,799
I'll go change my robes.

298
00:12:07,159 --> 00:12:08,080
We'll talk after I see His Majesty.

299
00:12:13,159 --> 00:12:14,279
You three, don't just sit idle.

300
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:15,559
Go out and find that bastard.

301
00:12:16,559 --> 00:12:18,080
Mother, why look for him?

302
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:19,440
Didn't we just drive him out?

303
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,480
And now we bring him back?

304
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,559
How did I bear such a foolish son?

305
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,799
No matter how lowly he is,

306
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:28,159
he's still your father's illegitimate son.

307
00:12:28,679 --> 00:12:30,200
If something happens to your father,

308
00:12:30,759 --> 00:12:32,120
you'd have to split the estate with him!

309
00:12:34,039 --> 00:12:34,639
Right, right, right.

310
00:12:34,799 --> 00:12:35,519
Mother's right.

311
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,120
As long as that brat lives,

312
00:12:37,679 --> 00:12:38,759
he's a threat.

313
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,639
Before, inside the manor,

314
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,159
we had to consider Father.

315
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:43,240
But now,

316
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:46,360
this is the perfect chance to kill him.

317
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,519
Mother, don't worry.

318
00:12:47,679 --> 00:12:48,519
I'll hire someone to finish him off.

319
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:51,679
Gan'er,

320
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,039
do not act yourself.

321
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,639
Though the written exam is over,

322
00:12:55,879 --> 00:12:57,200
you must still enter officialdom

323
00:12:57,399 --> 00:12:58,200
and take the palace exam.

324
00:12:58,559 --> 00:12:59,919
Do not give others any pretext.

325
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:00,759
I understand, Mother.

326
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:03,399
Go on then.

327
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,120
I understand. Thank you, Mother.

328
00:13:13,879 --> 00:13:16,080
And that's how the situation is.

329
00:13:17,919 --> 00:13:18,440
Young master,

330
00:13:18,799 --> 00:13:21,440
since when did you learn to write poetry?

331
00:13:21,879 --> 00:13:24,320
You barely had schooling at Ning manor.

332
00:13:25,279 --> 00:13:27,200
Perhaps when it comes to poetry,

333
00:13:27,399 --> 00:13:28,440
I happen to be quite gifted.

334
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,440
Travels with a eunuch in tow...

335
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:36,759
Could it be Prince Fu?

336
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:37,559
Bah!

337
00:13:37,799 --> 00:13:38,600
You little brat.

338
00:13:38,799 --> 00:13:40,639
Do you know the perils of the battlefield?

339
00:13:41,159 --> 00:13:42,320
This old man believes that this time,

340
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:44,080
you merely got lucky.

341
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,840
Who says I don't know the battlefield?

342
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:49,639
Then this old man shall test you.

343
00:13:52,759 --> 00:13:53,600
Bring it on.

